  <caaml:metaData>
    <caaml:comment>HS is 120, I just want to the scale to be 200cm so I can compare pits over time as things get deeper...&#13;
&#13;
The peculiar piece on this pit was just how big (2-3mm) the facets are between the Oct crusts and the Nov (Thanksgiving) crusts. Totally junk and not inspiring. The thing is, that I bet the Thanksgiving era crusts can hold a LOT of load before failing on these grains. Naturally the hope is that:&#13;
A) this is a localized snowpack structure &amp; not widespread &#13;
B) these facets begin to sinter before they ever see any real load.&#13;
Lot's of talk about the DDL beginning to heal in this part of the range. We will see, but the ECT result still shows propagation and every day we seem to get a random report of activity.</caaml:comment>
  </caaml:metaData>
